The MHD of Prague takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, it is written in the history of the Prague Transport Company the date when the first passengers enter the metro, the tram and the bus with an electronic bonus in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can be purchased at the moment by almost a hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase the 30 days, 90 days and the annual bonus (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and simultaneously charge it on their chip card at the transport company’s infocenters and positions at the metro stations, Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
The bonuses can be purchased on the website of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
The service, until the afternoon, was used by more than 400 people.
Those who begin to use the internet as a form of trade, can definitely begin to forget the ticket stations at the subway stations, where until now they had to regularly make a tail to get out a normal ticket.
The bonus is purchased on the internet, and the Opencard card is charged in some of the 13 subsidiaries of the Municipal Library.
“In these places there is available to passengers a window with prepared staff that helps those interested with the online purchase and also with the recharge of the bonus purchased on their card,” said project spokesman, Martin Opatrný.
Apart from the library, it will also be possible to recharge the electronic bonus on the Opencard on the expenditure automatic machines that are in some metro vestibules.
How are these expenditure machines?
They are red, they remind us of a ticket picking machine and travelers will probably have already fixed on them at the metro stations of Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
“Now there are five in the city but at the end of the year it would have to be eight,” Opatrný completed.
The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver.
The use of the machine, which will begin to work tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter the Opencard chip card and the previously paid bonus will be charged only on it.
Electronic bonuses from tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is, in the circumvalation trains and bus lines from the numbers 300 to 499 that are mainly used by the inhabitants of central Bohemia locations.
“In the trains attributed to Prague’s integrated transport there are revisors equipped with a reader card that will help confirm the validity of the time and the bonus area,” the bill control officer, Filip Drápal of the organization Ropid, who establishes Prague’s collective transport schedules, said.
Circumvalation buses have their reader cards mounted on the driver's ticket.
When entering it is necessary not only to show the card to the driver but also it is necessary to accompany him with the Opencard in the place intended for it on the side of the Box.
Thus, the driver controls the validity of the bonus.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the bonuses there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this information," Drápal added.
Passengers who do not travel in the circumvalation buses and don’t remember when they’re ending the validity of the bonus can go to the expenditure machines where the cards are charged.
